<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="335" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,852,1128]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,924,949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace with five anterolateral teeth, the last one twice as long as the others; four frontal teeth. Right cheliped larger than the left one, both with carinae and spines (Tavares, 2003; 
<bibRefCitation author="Torres" box="[1096,1305,959,984]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" refString="Torres, M. F. A., Ramos-Porto, M., Viana, G. F. S., Coelho, P. A., Botter-Carvalho, M. L. &amp; Santos, M. C. F. (2006) Redescricao e ocorrencia de Bathynectes longispina Stimpson, 1871 em aguas do Nordeste Brasileiro (Decapoda; Portunidae). Boletim Tecnico Cientifico do Cepnor, Belem, 6 (1), 133 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.17080 / 1676 - 5664 / btcc. v 6 n 1 p 133 - 140" type="journal article" year="2006">
Torres 
<emphasis box="[1173,1223,960,984]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="335" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,852,1128]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,996,1021]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[362,625,996,1020]" class="Malacostraca" family="Polybiidae" genus="Bathynectes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longispina">
<emphasis box="[362,625,996,1020]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">Bathynectes longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously reported for the east coast of North America, Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[151,236,1031,1056]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">
<collectingCountry box="[151,236,1031,1056]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">Mexico</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[296,355,1031,1056]" name="Cuba" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">Cuba</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Powers" box="[373,533,1032,1056]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" refString="Powers, L. W. (1977) A catalogue and bibliography to the crabs (Brachyura) of the Gulf of Mexico. Contributions in Marine Sci ence, 20 (Supplement), 1 - 190." type="journal article" year="1977">Powers, 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Manning" box="[547,862,1031,1056]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" refString="Manning, R. B. &amp; Holthuis, L. B. (1981) West African brachyuran crabs. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 306, 1 - 379." type="journal article" year="1981">Manning &amp; Holthuis, 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ingle" box="[876,1010,1031,1056]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" refString="Ingle, R. W. (1985) Geryon gordonae sp. nov. (Decapoda, Brachyura, Geryonidae) from the Northeastern Atlantic Ocean. Crustaceana, 48 (1), 88 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 156854085 X 00747" type="journal article" year="1985">Ingle, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). It was later also found in Brazilian waters (Tavares, 2003; 
<bibRefCitation author="Torres" box="[412,620,1068,1093]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335" refString="Torres, M. F. A., Ramos-Porto, M., Viana, G. F. S., Coelho, P. A., Botter-Carvalho, M. L. &amp; Santos, M. C. F. (2006) Redescricao e ocorrencia de Bathynectes longispina Stimpson, 1871 em aguas do Nordeste Brasileiro (Decapoda; Portunidae). Boletim Tecnico Cientifico do Cepnor, Belem, 6 (1), 133 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.17080 / 1676 - 5664 / btcc. v 6 n 1 p 133 - 140" type="journal article" year="2006">
Torres 
<emphasis box="[490,539,1068,1092]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
). This was the first time the species was collected at 
<collectionCode box="[1211,1291,1068,1092]" pageId="4" pageNumber="335">SPSPA</collectionCode>
representing a new record for the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
