<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens examined herein fit well with the descriptions provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson" box="[1236,1432,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" refString="Stimpson, W. (1871) Notes on North American Crustacea, in the museum of the Smithsonian Institution (N o III). Annals of the Lyceum of Natural History in New York, 10, 119 - 163." type="journal article" year="1871">Stimpson (1871)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rathbun" box="[151,332,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" refString="Rathbun, M. J. (1930) The Cancridae and Xanthidae. U. S Natural Museum Bulletin, 152, 1 - 609." type="journal article" year="1930">Rathbun (1930)</bibRefCitation>
, the later as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[484,607,188,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Polybiidae" genus="Bathynectes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="superba">
<emphasis box="[484,607,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">B. superba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and Tavares (2003). As pointed out by Tavares (2003), our material is similar to the material collected from 
<collectingRegion box="[589,751,223,248]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
state, which has the chelipeds unequal, the right one being larger than the left one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,392]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336">
A total of 
<specimenCount box="[315,468,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" type="generic">15 specimens</specimenCount>
were collected. Eight were analyzed, being two males and six females, with carapace lengths ranging from 
<quantity box="[402,596,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.175" metricValueMax="6.94" metricValueMin="5.41" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" unit="mm" value="61.75" valueMax="69.4" valueMin="54.1">54.1 to 69.4 mm</quantity>
CL and width from 
<quantity box="[841,1035,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.765" metricValueMax="9.95" metricValueMin="7.58" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" unit="mm" value="87.65" valueMax="99.5" valueMin="75.8">75.8 to 99.5 mm</quantity>
CW. For females the width of the abdomen ranged from 
<quantity box="[405,572,367,392]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.279999999999999" metricValueMax="4.46" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="336" unit="mm" value="42.8" valueMax="44.6" valueMin="41.0">41 to 44.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
